# images/etc.jffs2 is committed on purpose: it is built from the overlay, which
# ships only wpa_supplicant.conf.example (placeholders), so it carries no real
# credentials. It is needed to flash the /etc partition piece by piece, and it
# is embedded in images/linux-esp32s3-native-full.bin anyway.
#
# ⚠️ WARNING — this used to leak. buildroot's target/ is incremental, and a
# stale target/etc/wpa_supplicant.conf holding a real SSID/PSK once got baked
# into this image. Before committing any regenerated image, ALWAYS verify:
#
#     strings images/*.bin images/etc.jffs2 | grep -iE 'your-ssid|your-psk'
#
# and delete build-buildroot-*/target/etc/wpa_supplicant.conf if it exists.
# WiFi is meant to be configured at runtime: `wifi connect "SSID" "pass"`.
